'''George Hunter''' (July 22, 1927 &ndash; December 14, 2004) was a [[boxing|boxer]] from [[South Africa]], who competed in the [[Light Heavyweight]] division during his career as an amateur. 

==Amateur career==
Hunter represented his native country at the [[Summer Olympics]] of [[Boxing at the 1948 Summer Olympics|1948]], and was awarded the [[Val Barker Trophy]] for Outstanding Boxer.  

He was born in [[Brakpan]].

